text: Jean-François Mancel Jean-François Mancel (born March 1, 1948 in Beauvais, Oise) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Oise department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:People from Beauvais Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
